# Backend Ingestion And Pipeline

## Local Database Safety

- NEVER run DB-mutating worker commands (`populate-local-db`, `run-migrations`, `execute-load-plan --apply`, `load-seed-bundle`, `rematerialize-stale`, `materialize-item-details`, `materialize-gap-links`, `synthesize-item-profiles`) without explicit user confirmation.
- The local Postgres database contains curated data that is expensive to rebuild. Accidentally running populate or migration commands can overwrite or corrupt it.
- Read-only commands (`staleness-report`, `validate-packet`, `export-seeds`, `normalize-packet`, `build-load-plan`) are safe without confirmation.
- When diagnosing deployment issues, inspect code, config, logs, and remote endpoints — do not replay the pipeline locally as a shortcut.

## Pipeline Discipline

- Prefer `raw payload -> typed packet -> normalization -> load plan -> execute` over ad hoc shortcuts.
- Do not let live LLM output write directly into canonical tables.
- Route metadata-only or low-evidence packets into review queues instead of pretending they are ready.
- Keep new candidate items in review unless they are already matched to a canonical item.
- Use subagents for schema review, extraction review, and entity-resolution review when a change crosses boundaries.
